The paper deals with image segmentation and natural language processing, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of embeddings and end-to-end trainable architecture suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of resolving referring expressions.
